text: Sadly, it's a parody post- there's never been a Vatican Women's Rifle Team. Photo is of Sisters of Divine Providence trying out new .22 calibre guns presented to them at camp Mishannock by Harrington & Richardson of Worcester, MA. https://www.gettyimages.com.au/detail/news-photo/sisters-of-divine-providence-set-their-sights-as-they-try-news-photo/517213432#/kingston-ma-sisters-of-divine-providence-set-their-sights-as-they-try-picture-id517213432 …

The Vatican Women’s Rifle Team disbanded in 1938 (Pope didn’t think it was good for the Church’s image). Sister Juliette (far right) left the order in 1942 to join the underground as a sharpshooter. She was credited with assassinating several Nazi officials. pic.twitter.com/luZUtOUGAm
